38int
39nvkm_output_dp_train(struct nvkm_output *base, u32 datarate, bool wait)
40{
41 struct nvkm_output_dp *outp = nvkm_output_dp(base);
42 bool retrain = true;
43 u8 link[2], stat[3];
44 u32 linkrate;
45 int ret, i;
46
47 /* check that the link is trained at a high enough rate */
48 ret = nvkm_rdaux(outp->aux, DPCD_LC00_LINK_BW_SET, link, 2);
49 if (ret) {
50 OUTP_DBG(&outp->base,
51 "failed to read link config, assuming no sink");
52 goto done;
53 }
54
55 linkrate = link[0] * 27000 * (link[1] & DPCD_LC01_LANE_COUNT_SET);
56 linkrate = (linkrate * 8) / 10; /* 8B/10B coding overhead */
57 datarate = (datarate + 9) / 10; /* -> decakilobits */
58 if (linkrate < datarate) {
59 OUTP_DBG(&outp->base, "link not trained at sufficient rate");
60 goto done;
61 }
62
63 /* check that link is still trained */
64 ret = nvkm_rdaux(outp->aux, DPCD_LS02, stat, 3);
65 if (ret) {
66 OUTP_DBG(&outp->base,
67 "failed to read link status, assuming no sink");
68 goto done;
69 }
70
71 if (stat[2] & DPCD_LS04_INTERLANE_ALIGN_DONE) {
72 for (i = 0; i < (link[1] & DPCD_LC01_LANE_COUNT_SET); i++) {
73 u8 lane = (stat[i >> 1] >> ((i & 1) * 4)) & 0x0f;
74 if (!(lane & DPCD_LS02_LANE0_CR_DONE) ||
75 !(lane & DPCD_LS02_LANE0_CHANNEL_EQ_DONE) ||
76 !(lane & DPCD_LS02_LANE0_SYMBOL_LOCKED)) {
77 OUTP_DBG(&outp->base,
78 "lane %d not equalised", lane);
79 goto done;
80 }
81 }
82 retrain = false;
83 } else {
84 OUTP_DBG(&outp->base, "no inter-lane alignment");
85 }
86
87done:
88 if (retrain || !atomic_read(&outp->lt.done)) {
89 /* no sink, but still need to configure source */
90 if (outp->dpcd[DPCD_RC00_DPCD_REV] == 0x00) {
91 outp->dpcd[DPCD_RC01_MAX_LINK_RATE] =
92 outp->base.info.dpconf.link_bw;
93 outp->dpcd[DPCD_RC02] =
94 outp->base.info.dpconf.link_nr;
95 }
96 atomic_set(&outp->lt.done, 0);
97 schedule_work(&outp->lt.work);
98 } else {
99 nvkm_notify_get(&outp->irq);
100 }
101
102 if (wait) {
103#ifdef __NetBSD__
104 spin_lock(&outp->lt.lock);
105 DRM_SPIN_TIMED_WAIT_UNTIL(ret, &outp->lt.wait, &outp->lt.lock,
106 msecs_to_jiffies(2000),
107 atomic_read(&outp->lt.done));
108 spin_unlock(&outp->lt.lock);
109 if (ret == 0) /* timeout */
110 ret = -ETIMEDOUT;
111 else if (ret > 0) /* success */
112 ret = 0;
113#else
114 if (!wait_event_timeout(outp->lt.wait,
115 atomic_read(&outp->lt.done),
116 msecs_to_jiffies(2000)))
117 ret = -ETIMEDOUT;
118#endif
119 }
120
121 return ret;
122}
123
124static void
125nvkm_output_dp_enable(struct nvkm_output_dp *outp, bool enable)
126{
127 struct nvkm_i2c_aux *aux = outp->aux;
128
129 if (enable) {
130 if (!outp->present) {
131 OUTP_DBG(&outp->base, "aux power -> always");
132 nvkm_i2c_aux_monitor(aux, true);
133 outp->present = true;
134 }
135
136 if (!nvkm_rdaux(aux, DPCD_RC00_DPCD_REV, outp->dpcd,
137 sizeof(outp->dpcd))) {
138 nvkm_output_dp_train(&outp->base, 0, true);
139 return;
140 }
141 }
142
143 if (outp->present) {
144 OUTP_DBG(&outp->base, "aux power -> demand");
145 nvkm_i2c_aux_monitor(aux, false);
146 outp->present = false;
147 }
148
149 atomic_set(&outp->lt.done, 0);
150}
151
152static int
153nvkm_output_dp_hpd(struct nvkm_notify *notify)
154{
155 const struct nvkm_i2c_ntfy_rep *line = notify->data;
156 struct nvkm_output_dp *outp = container_of(notify, typeof(*outp), hpd);
157 struct nvkm_connector *conn = outp->base.conn;
158 struct nvkm_disp *disp = outp->base.disp;
159 struct nvif_notify_conn_rep_v0 rep = {};
160
161 OUTP_DBG(&outp->base, "HPD: %d", line->mask);
162 nvkm_output_dp_enable(outp, true);
163
164 if (line->mask & NVKM_I2C_UNPLUG)
165 rep.mask |= NVIF_NOTIFY_CONN_V0_UNPLUG;
166 if (line->mask & NVKM_I2C_PLUG)
167 rep.mask |= NVIF_NOTIFY_CONN_V0_PLUG;
168
169 nvkm_event_send(&disp->hpd, rep.mask, conn->index, &rep, sizeof(rep));
170 return NVKM_NOTIFY_KEEP;
171}
172
173static int
174nvkm_output_dp_irq(struct nvkm_notify *notify)
175{
176 const struct nvkm_i2c_ntfy_rep *line = notify->data;
177 struct nvkm_output_dp *outp = container_of(notify, typeof(*outp), irq);
178 struct nvkm_connector *conn = outp->base.conn;
179 struct nvkm_disp *disp = outp->base.disp;
180 struct nvif_notify_conn_rep_v0 rep = {
181 .mask = NVIF_NOTIFY_CONN_V0_IRQ,
182 };
183
184 OUTP_DBG(&outp->base, "IRQ: %d", line->mask);
185 nvkm_output_dp_train(&outp->base, 0, true);
186
187 nvkm_event_send(&disp->hpd, rep.mask, conn->index, &rep, sizeof(rep));
188 return NVKM_NOTIFY_DROP;
189}
190
191static void
192nvkm_output_dp_fini(struct nvkm_output *base)
193{
194 struct nvkm_output_dp *outp = nvkm_output_dp(base);
195 nvkm_notify_put(&outp->hpd);
196 nvkm_notify_put(&outp->irq);
197 flush_work(&outp->lt.work);
198 nvkm_output_dp_enable(outp, false);
199}
200
201static void
202nvkm_output_dp_init(struct nvkm_output *base)
203{
204 struct nvkm_output_dp *outp = nvkm_output_dp(base);
205 nvkm_notify_put(&outp->base.conn->hpd);
206 nvkm_output_dp_enable(outp, true);
207 nvkm_notify_get(&outp->hpd);
208}
209
210static void *
211nvkm_output_dp_dtor(struct nvkm_output *base)
212{
213 struct nvkm_output_dp *outp = nvkm_output_dp(base);
214 nvkm_notify_fini(&outp->hpd);
215 nvkm_notify_fini(&outp->irq);
216#ifndef __NetBSD__
217 spin_lock_destroy(&outp->lt.lock);
218 DRM_DESTROY_WAITQUEUE(&outp->lt.wait);
219#endif
220 return outp;
221}
222
223static const struct nvkm_output_func
224nvkm_output_dp_func = {
225 .dtor = nvkm_output_dp_dtor,
226 .init = nvkm_output_dp_init,
227 .fini = nvkm_output_dp_fini,
228};
229
230int
231nvkm_output_dp_ctor(const struct nvkm_output_dp_func *func,
232 struct nvkm_disp *disp, int index, struct dcb_output *dcbE,
233 struct nvkm_i2c_aux *aux, struct nvkm_output_dp *outp)
234{
235 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->engine.subdev.device;
236 struct nvkm_bios *bios = device->bios;
237 struct nvkm_i2c *i2c = device->i2c;
238 u8 hdr, cnt, len;
239 u32 data;
240 int ret;
241
242 nvkm_output_ctor(&nvkm_output_dp_func, disp, index, dcbE, &outp->base);
243 outp->func = func;
244 outp->aux = aux;
245 if (!outp->aux) {
246 OUTP_ERR(&outp->base, "no aux");
247 return -ENODEV;
248 }
249
250 /* bios data is not optional */
251 data = nvbios_dpout_match(bios, outp->base.info.hasht,
252 outp->base.info.hashm, &outp->version,
253 &hdr, &cnt, &len, &outp->info);
254 if (!data) {
255 OUTP_ERR(&outp->base, "no bios dp data");
256 return -ENODEV;
257 }
258
259 OUTP_DBG(&outp->base, "bios dp %02x %02x %02x %02x",
260 outp->version, hdr, cnt, len);
261
262 /* link training */
263 INIT_WORK(&outp->lt.work, nvkm_dp_train);
264#ifdef __NetBSD__
265 DRM_INIT_WAITQUEUE(&outp->lt.wait, "nvoutpdp");
266 spin_lock_init(&outp->lt.lock);
267#else
268 init_waitqueue_head(&outp->lt.wait);
269#endif
270 atomic_set(&outp->lt.done, 0);
271
272 /* link maintenance */
273 ret = nvkm_notify_init(NULL, &i2c->event, nvkm_output_dp_irq, true,
274 &(struct nvkm_i2c_ntfy_req) {
275 .mask = NVKM_I2C_IRQ,
276 .port = outp->aux->id,
277 },
278 sizeof(struct nvkm_i2c_ntfy_req),
279 sizeof(struct nvkm_i2c_ntfy_rep),
280 &outp->irq);
281 if (ret) {
282 OUTP_ERR(&outp->base, "error monitoring aux irq: %d", ret);
283 return ret;
284 }
285
286 /* hotplug detect, replaces gpio-based mechanism with aux events */
287 ret = nvkm_notify_init(NULL, &i2c->event, nvkm_output_dp_hpd, true,
288 &(struct nvkm_i2c_ntfy_req) {
289 .mask = NVKM_I2C_PLUG | NVKM_I2C_UNPLUG,
290 .port = outp->aux->id,
291 },
292 sizeof(struct nvkm_i2c_ntfy_req),
293 sizeof(struct nvkm_i2c_ntfy_rep),
294 &outp->hpd);
295 if (ret) {
296 OUTP_ERR(&outp->base, "error monitoring aux hpd: %d", ret);
297 return ret;
298 }
299
300 return 0;
301}
302
303int
304nvkm_output_dp_new_(const struct nvkm_output_dp_func *func,
305 struct nvkm_disp *disp, int index, struct dcb_output *dcbE,
306 struct nvkm_output **poutp)
307{
308 struct nvkm_i2c *i2c = disp->engine.subdev.device->i2c;
309 struct nvkm_i2c_aux *aux = nvkm_i2c_aux_find(i2c, dcbE->i2c_index);
310 struct nvkm_output_dp *outp;
311
312 if (!(outp = kzalloc(sizeof(*outp), GFP_KERNEL)))
313 return -ENOMEM;
314 *poutp = &outp->base;
315
316 return nvkm_output_dp_ctor(func, disp, index, dcbE, aux, outp);
317}
